@Agents_HostAddress = http://localhost:5118
@conversationId = 11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111
@projectId = 22222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222222

### 1. Requirements chat — send a turn. Repeat with more detail until isMatched=true.
POST {{Agents_HostAddress}}/project/chat
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "conversation_id": "{{conversationId}}",
  "project_id": "{{projectId}}",
  "message": "I want to build a web-based e-commerce store with a product catalog, cart, and Stripe checkout for about 10,000 customers. Tech stack is React and ASP.NET. Roles are customer and admin. Needs OAuth2 security, p95 < 300ms, 99.9% availability."
}

### 2. Modules estimation — paste a completed ProjectChatResponse (from step 1's matched reply).
POST {{Agents_HostAddress}}/project/modules
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "conversation_id": "{{conversationId}}",
  "project_id": "{{projectId}}",
  "isMatched": true,
  "response": "ok",
  "projectDetails": {
    "projectObjective": "Build an online store",
    "scope": ["catalog", "cart", "checkout"],
    "platform": "Web",
    "technologyStack": ["React", "ASP.NET"],
    "integrations": ["Stripe"],
    "userRoles": ["customer", "admin"],
    "expectedUsers": "10000",
    "securityRequirements": ["OAuth2"],
    "performanceRequirements": "p95 < 300ms",
    "availabilityRequirements": "99.9%"
  },
  "missingRequirements": []
}

### 3. Orchestrate — routes to the requirements tool (gathering intent).
POST {{Agents_HostAddress}}/project/orchestrate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "conversation_id": "{{conversationId}}",
  "project_id": "{{projectId}}",
  "message": "Here is my project: a web store with catalog and Stripe checkout."
}

### 4. Orchestrate — routes to the modules tool (once requirements are complete).
POST {{Agents_HostAddress}}/project/orchestrate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "conversation_id": "{{conversationId}}",
  "project_id": "{{projectId}}",
  "message": "Looks good, please estimate the modules now."
}

### 5. Chat history — ordered messages for the frontend.
GET {{Agents_HostAddress}}/project/{{conversationId}}/history
Accept: application/json

### 6. Full snapshot — requirements + modules + messages for a conversation.
GET {{Agents_HostAddress}}/project/{{conversationId}}
Accept: application/json
